 nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-2.19b27 by                    6249 1451
 M. Herman et al [He01, He02]. This code integrates               6249 1451
 into a single system a number of important modules               6249 1451
 and features:                                                    6249 1451
                                                                  6249 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 6249 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS03 by J. Raynal)                         6249 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    6249 1451
   HRTW width fluctuation correction                              6249 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                6249 1451
   TRISTAN by H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                      6249 1451
 - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling                   6249 1451
   (code DEGAS by E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that                6249 1451
   represents a good approximation to the DSD model               6249 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      6249 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 6249 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                6249 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   6249 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                6249 1451
   discrete transitions                                           6249 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03]              6249 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                6249 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               6249 1451
   and gamma strength functions  based on the RIPL-2              6249 1451
   library [Ri03]                                                 6249 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              6249 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           6249 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov)                    6249 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 6249 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                6249 1451
